From 270cfac42f41cee6880d1ee00aa29e6b8c7666b4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jason Gross <jason@theorem.dev>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 19:48:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] arm: avoid brace-initializer re-assignment in
 gfunc_prolog under BOOTSTRAP
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Under -D BOOTSTRAP=1, AVAIL_REGS_INITIALIZER expands to {0}, so the
bare re-assignment `avregs = AVAIL_REGS_INITIALIZER;` becomes
`avregs = {0};` — invalid C (a brace initializer is only legal in a
declaration). GCC accepts it, but MesCC's nyacc parser rejects it:

    parse failed at state 367, on input {

making tcc.c uncompilable by MesCC whenever TCC_TARGET_ARM and
TCC_ARM_EABI are set. The analogous compound-literal declarations in
assign_regs are already #if !BOOTSTRAP-guarded; this lone use-site was
missed. Use a temporary declaration under BOOTSTRAP instead.

Verified: with this (and the following TOK___memmove fix), MesCC
running on an armv7l mes-m2 compiles the full tcc.c (TCC_TARGET_ARM=1
TCC_ARM_EABI=1 TCC_ARM_VFP=1 BOOTSTRAP=1 ONE_SOURCE=1) and the
resulting tcc runs on AArch32.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_0135X6tRviSFCswBbHXxQofc
---
 arm-gen.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arm-gen.c b/arm-gen.c
index 42a334c9..eaddad31 100644
--- a/arm-gen.c
+++ b/arm-gen.c
@@ -1368,7 +1368,11 @@ void gfunc_prolog(CType *func_type)
 #ifdef TCC_ARM_EABI
   if (float_abi == ARM_HARD_FLOAT) {
     func_vc += nf * 4;
+#if !BOOTSTRAP
     avregs = AVAIL_REGS_INITIALIZER;
+#else
+    { struct avail_regs _tmp = AVAIL_REGS_INITIALIZER; avregs = _tmp; }
+#endif
   }
 #endif
   pn = struct_ret, sn = 0;
